Usage: taup table [--debug] [--help] [--header=<headerFile>]
                  [--prop=<toolPropsFilename>] [-p=<phaseNames>[,
                  <phaseNames>...]]... [[-mod=<modelname>] [-h=<sourceDepth>]
                  [--stadepth=depth] [--scat=s s]...] [--text | --json | --csv
                  | --locsat]
create a table of travel times for a range of depths and distances
      --debug             display debugging message
      --header=<headerFile>
                          reads depth and distance spacing data
                                                from a LOCSAT style file.
      --help              display this help message
  -p, --ph, --phase=<phaseNames>[,<phaseNames>...]
                          seismic phase names
      --prop=<toolPropsFilename>
                          load defaults from properties file
Model Args
  -h, --sourcedepth=<sourceDepth>
                          source depth in km
      -mod, --mod, --model=<modelname>
                          use velocity model "modelname" for calculations
                                                Default is iasp91.
      --scat, --scatter=s s
                          scattering depth and distance in degrees, which may
                            be negative.
      --stadepth=depth    the receiver depth in km for stations not at the
                            surface
Output Type
      --csv               outputs as CSV
      --json              outputs as JSON
      --locsat            outputs as locsat
      --text, --generic   outputs as text
